																		Merry Christmas Coldpost
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225812" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1450921703 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Dec 2015 01:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2428817">
									

<p>I usually don't do this, but since it's the Christmas season and me living in the not-cold tropics, I need some coldness in my life. Hence the coldpost as my little something for Christmas!</p>
<p>SCPs mentioned here include: SCP-055 by qntm</p>
<p>The Hu siblings are taken from <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/wrong-analytics">my author page</a>.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>SCP-055 is not round. Since it is an anti-meme that hides its own traits, what if the one trait we all know it to not be is actually 055's most definitive trait (being round).</p>
<p>Ergo, SCP-055 is actually round.</p>
<p>For elaboration,</p>
<p>055 has been called a weak anti-meme, since we can still know that it is at least known. If it really was a weak anti-meme, 055 would be doing a shitty job at obscuring itself. While that is usually represented by &quot;We can deduce what it is not&quot; logic, this rides on the &quot;a weak anti-meme that somehow has everyone remember just one trait that it actually has yet has it framed it as what it should not be&quot;.</p>
<p>e.g. Santa!055 is actually round –&gt; Person sees Santa!055 –&gt; Person forgets everything about Santa!055 due to antimemetic aspects, except the roundness (due to weak anti-meme) –&gt; Antimemetic aspects still manage to force Person to dismiss roundness as a trait Santa!055 does not have –&gt; Person says, &quot;Santa!055 is not round&quot;.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
