															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225812" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1450954809 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Dec 2015 11:00</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2428920">
									

<blockquote>
<p>055 is not a sphere.<br />
And Santa is not a sphere either.<br />
Ergo, Santa is 055.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>By that logic, everything not spherical is 055.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Besides, it'll be the Sites for us on the 26th</p>
</blockquote>
<p>26th of December, where the normal working day resumes. Okay, the Foundation is most likely operational 24/7, but I guess selected staff are allowed leave for Christmas Eve and Day.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I must say I don't quite understand the link between the two parts of your tale (Santa -&gt; the Hu family), but… hey, why not?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The transition is that the former is essentially a random story conjured up by Hu Zhi to kill time. I wanted to have the earlier part only originally, but I can't pass the chance to lampoon something I wrote. And holidays are meant for people to gather and do stuff together, even if they are part of a secret inter-governmental organisation.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Oh, BTW: I'm rather surprised that Santa Claus is not already an SCP with its own huge canon hub… Or have I not searched properly? ;&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I know&#8230; Santa can be so many things.</p>

							</div>

								
